  "directional_assessment": {
    "median_run_length_scenes_stable": "Median POV-run length (in scenes) is 1.0 / 1 / 1 (cs / sos / hg) -- crystal_shard and halflings_gem are nearly identical at ~1 scene, streams_of_silver at 2 scenes. Means are 1.16 / 1.33 / 1.17.",
    "median_run_length_beats_caveat": "Median POV-run length in beats is 6.0 / 8 / 5 -- streams_of_silver appears longer mostly because its scenes are systematically larger (median 952w/scene vs ~488-565w in the other two books, a known scene-segmentation artifact also flagged in Pattern 22). For cross-book comparison, the scenes-unit median is the cleaner signal.",
    "drizzt_lead_share_stable": "Drizzt's POV share is remarkably stable across the trilogy: 27% / 34% / 32% of beats (cs / sos / hg). Lead-character POV concentration is a corpus-wide structural signal, not a one-off.",
    "single_scene_runs": "Single-scene POV runs (one scene then rotate) comprise 86% / 79% / 87% of all POV runs. Multi-scene POV runs (3+ scenes) comprise 2% / 7% / 3%.",
    "headline": "POV rotation is fast: median 1-2 scenes per POV-hold across the trilogy. Salvatore alternates between threads at scene boundaries far more often than holding one POV for chapter-long chunks. Drizzt is the lead-POV at ~25-29% of all beats in every book, with secondary POVs (Bruenor / Wulfgar / Regis) splitting most of the remainder. Book-1-specific POVs (Akar Kessell, Heafstaag) appear and Books-2/3-specific POVs (Artemis Entreri, Pasha Pook) appear, matching known plot structure."
  },
  "harness_target": {
    "planner_section": "src/agents/planning-plotter/chapter-outline-system.md (per-chapter POV slot + intra-chapter rotation guidance).",
    "recommended_prior": "POV-rotation prior: median POV-run is 1-2 scenes (i.e., a POV holds for 1 scene, occasionally 2 scenes, before rotating). Long single-POV runs (>=4 scenes / 8+ beats) are uncommon (~25-30% of runs). At the chapter-outline granularity, the planner should NOT enforce one-POV-per-chapter -- instead, allow 2-3 POV slots per chapter, with the lead character (the seed protagonist) holding ~25-29% of total beats and 4-5 secondary POVs splitting the remainder. Pair with Pattern 22 (ensemble size) since both inform the planner's character-presence prior.",
    "ship_status": "Candidate ship -- directional signal is clean across all three books: median POV-run 1-2 scenes, lead-POV share 25-29%, distribution shape (single-scene runs dominant + 3+ scene runs uncommon) reproducing in every book. Note that the streams_of_silver beat-level numbers are inflated by scene-segmentation differences and should NOT be used cross-book without normalization."
  }
}